# Sheaf API scratchpad — VS Code "REST Client" extension / IntelliJ HTTP client.
# Fire requests top to bottom; paste ids from responses into the variables.
# Full contract: docs/API.md

@base = http://localhost:3000
@worldId = PASTE-WORLD-ID
@entryId = PASTE-ENTRY-ID
@crsId = PASTE-CRS-ID
@calendarId = PASTE-CALENDAR-ID
@typeId = PASTE-RELATION-TYPE-ID

### Health
GET {{base}}/healthz

### ---------- Worlds ----------

### Create world
POST {{base}}/worlds
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Aldervane" }

### List worlds
GET {{base}}/worlds

### Get / rename / delete
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}

### Rename
PATCH {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Aldervane Reborn" }

### Delete (cascades entries, artifacts, stored objects)
DELETE {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}

### ---------- World config ----------

### Create CRS
POST {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/crs
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "main", "params": { "projection": "equirectangular" } }

### Create calendar (arithmetic)
POST {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/calendars
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "common reckoning",
  "type": "arithmetic",
  "definition": { "months": [ { "name": "Frostwane", "days": 30 }, { "name": "Sunreach", "days": 30 } ] }
}

### Create calendar (ordinal, anchored + unanchored stages)
POST {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/calendars
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "the ages",
  "type": "ordinal",
  "definition": { "stages": [ { "name": "First Age", "tickStart": 0, "tickEnd": 10000 }, { "name": "Age of Mist" } ] }
}

### Create relation type
POST {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/relation-types
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "located-in", "inverseName": "contains" }

### Lists
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/crs

###
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/calendars

###
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/relation-types

### ---------- Entries ----------

### Create entry
POST {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/entries
Content-Type: application/json

{ "type": "region", "title": "The Shattered Coast", "tags": ["coastal", "ruined"] }

### List (filters: ?type=&tag=&limit=&cursor=)
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/entries?limit=10

### Detail — aggregates tags + all artifact metadata
GET {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}

### Update
PATCH {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "title": "The Shattered Coast, Reforged" }

### Replace tag set
PUT {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/tags
Content-Type: application/json

{ "tags": ["coastal", "reborn"] }

### Delete
DELETE {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}

### ---------- Artifact lifecycle (documents shown; images/sketches/geometries identical) ----------
# Step 1 — create returns { upload: { url } }. Step 2 — PUT payload to that
# URL (raw HTTP, not this API). Step 3 — finalize.

### 1. Create document
POST {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json

{ "role": "body", "label": "main text" }

### 2. Upload — paste the presigned URL from the response above
PUT PASTE-UPLOAD-URL
Content-Type: text/markdown

# The Shattered Coast

Salt and ruin.

### 3. Finalize (validates payload, derives search index / bbox / thumbnail)
POST {{base}}/documents/PASTE-DOC-ID/finalize

### Read back (download = presigned GET; pending/failed → download null)
GET {{base}}/documents/PASTE-DOC-ID

### Fresh upload window (revive failed artifact, or replace content)
POST {{base}}/documents/PASTE-DOC-ID/upload-url

### Create image (finalize also derives a ≤512px webp thumbnail)
POST {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/images
Content-Type: application/json

{ "contentType": "image/png", "label": "banner" }

### Create sketch (payload must be Excalidraw scene JSON)
POST {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/sketches
Content-Type: application/json

{ "label": "tavern layout" }

### Create geometry (payload must be GeoJSON Feature/FeatureCollection)
POST {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/geometries
Content-Type: application/json

{ "crsId": "{{crsId}}", "label": "territory" }

### ---------- Date ranges ----------

### Create (server computes ticks; see docs/API.md appendix)
POST {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/date-ranges
Content-Type: application/json

{ "calendarId": "{{calendarId}}", "rawComponents": { "year": 2, "month": 1, "day": 1 }, "precisionTier": "exact" }

### ---------- Relations ----------

### Create edge
POST {{base}}/relations
Content-Type: application/json

{ "fromId": "{{entryId}}", "toId": "PASTE-OTHER-ENTRY-ID", "typeId": "{{typeId}}" }

### List an entry's edges (?direction=out|in|both&typeId=)
GET {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/relations?direction=both

### Graph traversal (?depth=1..5&direction=&typeId=)
GET {{base}}/entries/{{entryId}}/graph?depth=2&direction=both

### ---------- Search ----------

### Full text (rank + highlighted snippets)
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/search?q=shattered

### Compose filters (all AND)
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/search?q=shattered&tag=coastal&type=region

### Geo bbox overlap — stage 1 GiST; add &exact=true for the turf stage-2 pass
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/search?bbox=5,5,15,15&crsId={{crsId}}

### Date overlap on the tick line
GET {{base}}/worlds/{{worldId}}/search?tickStart=50&tickEnd=70
